<!-- ========== WHAT WE REVIEW ========== -->
<section class="lp-what">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Every detail evaluated</h2>
        <p class="lp-what__intro">
            Being technically correct is the baseline. High-impact journals look for
            something harder to fake: <strong>Strategic Coherence</strong> —
            the alignment between your question, your design, and your analysis,
            from the very first paragraph.
        </p>
        <div class="lp-what__grid">
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">⚗️</div>
                <h3>Methodology</h3>
                <p>Analysis validity, bias identification, instrument alignment, and sampling adequacy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">✍️</div>
                <h3>Language</h3>
                <p>Scientific writing quality, active voice preference, vocabulary precision, and dialect adequacy for your target journal.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">📐</div>
                <h3>Formatting</h3>
                <p>Paragraph structure, section length, and editorial compliance with international reporting standards.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">🎯</div>
                <h3>Competitive Positioning</h3>
                <p>Innovation assessment, literature saturation, and relevance for the journal you're targeting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">📄</div>
                <h3>Content Coherence</h3>
                <p>Capacity to answer its own research question, data grounding, and literature alignment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="lp-what__card">
                <div class="lp-what__icon">🌐</div>
                <h3>International Standards</h3>
                <p>Compliance with PRISMA, CONSORT, STROBE, GRADE, and other applicable guidelines.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

